        <div class="lesson-content">
          <h3>10. expand and unexpand</h3>
          <p class="lesson-text"><p>In our lesson on the cut command, we had our sample.txt file that contained a tab. Normally TABs would usually show a noticeable difference but some text files don't show that well enough. Having TABs in a text file may not be the desired spacing you want. To change your TABs to spaces, use the expand command. </p>

<p><pre>$ expand sample.txt</pre></p>

<p>The command above will print output with each TAB converted into a group of spaces. To save this output in a file, use output redirection like below.</p>

<p><pre>$ expand sample.txt &gt; result.txt</pre></p>

<p>Opposite to expand, we can convert back each group of spaces to a TAB with the unexpand command: </p>

<p><pre>$ unexpand -a result.txt</pre></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
